<a name="newsitem951879156,86537,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Golden Efreeti Gauntlets</font> </strong><small>Posted Tuesday, February 29, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
I just posted up some new gloves from the Plane of Air. That's four pieces of the Golden Efreeti armor so far. Just need a helmet, bracer and breastplate now. =) <br><br>New Equipment: <a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/goldenefreetigauntlets.html">Golden Efreeti Gauntlets</a>.
</p>
<a name="newsitem951876527,26311,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Links To NPCs</font> </strong><small>Posted Tuesday, February 29, 2000 by <a href="mailto:bucksatan@gameznet.com">Buck Satan</a></small><br>
I keyed in URLs tonight for all of the NPCs listed in the EQCompendium searches over at <a href="http://www.gamezportal.com/eqr">EQ Reference</a>.  Now, when you search for armor, weapons, or miscellaneous equipment, there will be a hyperlink to the appropriate spawn page in the beastiary (assuming the NPC has its own page).  Nothing too phenomenal, but still pretty cool.  <br><br>I'd also like to mention that I'm flying out tomorrow for Mardi Gras 2000 and will be gone for a week of drunken debauchery.  Feel free to email additions or corrections for the spawn guides, etc and I will post them up as soon as I get back.  Groovy. 
</p>
<a name="newsitem951859980,1773,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Equipment Update</font> </strong><small>Posted Tuesday, February 29, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
Alright finally cleaned out the equipment from the mailbox. Still need to go through the quests but here's four new pieces of equipment and two screenshots for older pieces of equipment that lacked them.<br><br>New Equipment: <a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/chrystalisman.html">Chrysoberyl Talisman</a>, <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/reddragontooth.html">Red Dragon Tooth</a>, <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/codeofzanfi.html">Code of Zan Fi</a>, <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/mithfrogtotem.html">Mithril Frog Totem</a>, <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/blacksilkgloves.html">Black Silk Gloves</a>, <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/goblinsticker.html">Goblin Sticker</a>(SHM).
</p>
<a name="newsitem951855976,8666,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Rat Bone Powder</font> </strong><small>Posted Tuesday, February 29, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
Lyssa sent in a screenshot of the <a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/ratbonepowder.html">Rat Bone Powder</a> which can be found off a rare in Dagnor's Cauldron. Nothing earth shattering but it's something that we didn't have listed. =) <br><br>New Equipment: <a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/ratbonepowder.html">Rat Bone Powder</a>.
</p>
<a name="newsitem951799927,19839,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Permafrost</font> </strong><small>Posted Monday, February 28, 2000 by <a href="mailto:bucksatan@gameznet.com">Buck Satan</a></small><br>
I have added Permafrost to the list of zones on the <a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/notsocommon.html">Not-So-Common Spawn Guide</a>.  I didn't list any of the giants or other high level critters enroute to Lady Vox, however, as they are unitemized.  If good screenshots are submitted for some of them tho (the IG Diplomat or Priest of Nagafen for example), I'll post them up.<br><br>Soon, I'm going to break down each of the different Planes in the same manner as the other guides.  I'm very familiar with all of the Fear and Hate spawns, but the PoA is pretty sketchy.  If someone has the time to put together and submit a list of spawns with the items they drop it would be much appreciated.  I'd rather have a good solid listing rather than post incorrect or missing information.
</p>
<a name="newsitem951774349,70568,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Quest Page Reorganized</font> </strong><small>Posted Monday, February 28, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
I finally got around to revamping the <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/quest.html">Quest</a> page. It was something that was long overdue. The quest page had grown to 80k and load times were getting a bit lengthy. Quests are now broken down by zone.<br><br>Updated Section: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/quest.html">Quests</a>.
</p>
<a name="newsitem951770130,20947,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Couple New Items</font> </strong><small>Posted Monday, February 28, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
I just added a couple of new items to the equipment section and the <a href="http://www.gamezportal.com/eqr">Advanced Searches</a>.<br><br>New Equipment: <a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/teschvalsinisch.html">Tesch Val Sinisch</a>(SHM), <a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/fieryvambraces.html">Fiery Vambraces</a>.
</p>
<a name="newsitem951766943,52327,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">One Year Down</font> </strong><small>Posted Monday, February 28, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
Today marks the one year anniversary of EQ'Lizer. Hard to believe it's been a year already. My how time flies when your having fun.<br><br>A year ago we were the only site which gave an extensive equipment and quest sections, we were the only site which had spells above level 20 posted for every class. Times have changed. Now you can browse through the net and find any number of sites which offer quests, daily equipment updates, zone guides, spells as well as news and our staff consisted of one person(myself).<br><br>At this time last year the game was on the closing days of beta testing. It had already gone gold and was readying a mid-march release. It has grown and matured much since then. In the initial months we were quite hard on Verant for in my opinion rushing the release. There are still certain moves that I might disagree with but all in all the game is vastly improved from a year ago.<br><br>I just wanted to take the time to thank all of the editors and readers who have been through these gates in the past year. All the editors have done a great job from Iuons to Fyndhorn to most recently Buck Satan and a good number of other editors(such as T and Welor) who are too many to mention. Thanks for making EQ'Lizer the site that it is today and here's to another year in operations.
</p>
<a name="newsitem951684396,37441,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Crushbone and Solusek A</font> </strong><small>Posted Sunday, February 27, 2000 by <a href="mailto:bucksatan@gameznet.com">Buck Satan</a></small><br>
Both Crushbone and Solusek A have been added to the <a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/notsocommon.html">Not-So-Common Spawn Guide</a>.  I've also been adding all the information being submitted to the <a href="http://www.gameznet.com/eq/ultra.html">Ultra Spawn Guide</a>, as well as a couple strategy guides.  Good stuff.  We could use more of the strategy guides tho, so keep them coming.
</p>
<a name="newsitem951677846,12301,"></a>
<p><strong><font color="#f0f0f0">Alchemy Guide Update</font> </strong><small>Posted Sunday, February 27, 2000 by <a href="mailto:jcsmith@gameznet.com">jcsmith</a></small><br>
Belazaar has sent in a new version of his <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/class/alchemy.html">Alchemy Guide</a>. Lots of good stuff inside for all you shamans out there.<br><br>Updated Skills Guide: <a href="http://gameznet.com/eq/class/alchemy.html">Alchemy</a>.
</p>
